695
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:04,700
And they tell you how the configuration changes.

696
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:06,540
And if you have good laws

697
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:07,960
in classical physics,

698
00:25:08,060 --> 00:25:08,920
they're deterministic.

699
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:11,340
They tell you how the state changes.

700
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:13,320
But also another rule,

701
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,520
and the other rule we called reversibility.

702
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:20,260
Reversibility was basically just the idea

703
00:25:20,260 --> 00:25:22,700
that states don't run into each other.

704
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:24,660
That states which are distinguishable,

705
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:26,120
namely different,

706
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:28,720
heads and tails are distinguishable,

707
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:32,380
are two states which are different,

708
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:35,340
will evolve mathematically

709
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:37,700
and stay different.

710
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:39,300
All right?

711
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:41,480
That was the idea of reversibility.

712
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,300
And what it comes down to

713
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:46,020
is exactly that,

714
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:48,420
that if you know the state at any instant,

715
00:25:48,540 --> 00:25:50,260
you not only will know what comes next,

716
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:52,420
but you will also know what came before,

717
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:54,600
because there's no chance

718
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:56,000
that states run together,

719
00:25:58,020 --> 00:25:59,640
and two different states

720
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:00,880
giving you the same outcome,

721
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:03,320
then you wouldn't be able to tell

722
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:04,020
where you came from.

723
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,720
So reversibility is the idea.

724
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,820
We also called it information conservation.

725
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:11,460
And I suspect I referred to it

726
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:13,060
as the minus first law.

727
00:26:13,860 --> 00:26:16,780
Minus first because it comes before everything else.

728
00:26:17,980 --> 00:26:21,080
Quantum mechanics also has a rule of

729
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:23,760
both reversibility and information conservation.

730
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:26,660
You can call it the minus first law.

731
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:30,740
But it comes down to the same thing.

732
00:26:31,700 --> 00:26:33,680
States which are distinguishable,

733
00:26:33,740 --> 00:26:34,940
in the sense that I said,

734
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,340
that there exists an experiment

735
00:26:36,340 --> 00:26:37,900
that uniquely distinguishes them,

736
00:26:38,020 --> 00:26:38,720
stay.

737
00:26:42,420 --> 00:26:42,900
Distinguishable.

738
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:44,440
Alright,

739
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,700
so now we want to talk about

740
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:48,440
how states evolve with time.

741
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:51,960
We're going to come back

742
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:56,060
and discuss this in the context of the spin.

