00:26:56,220 --> 00:26:58,140
It's the simplest system of quantum mechanics,

744
00:26:58,200 --> 00:26:59,090
and it's a good idea to

745
00:26:59,090 --> 00:26:59,980
get it all down for that.

746
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:02,320
But let's talk about it more generally.

747
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:04,380
Okay.

748
00:27:05,220 --> 00:27:06,280
Here's the postulate.

749
00:27:07,379 --> 00:27:08,640
The postulate is

750
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:10,860
that if you have a system

751
00:27:10,860 --> 00:27:11,980
at time,

752
00:27:11,980 --> 00:27:13,480
at some specific time,

753
00:27:13,660 --> 00:27:15,480
let's call it a time zero.

754
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:18,280
And I'm going to start changing

755
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:19,860
my notation for states.

756
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,480
Instead of calling them A and B,

757
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:24,700
I'm going to start using a notation

758
00:27:24,700 --> 00:27:27,300
which is more or less a standard notation

759
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:28,280
in quantum mechanics.

760
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:30,180
Call them psi.

761
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,360
Psi is a Greek letter.

762
00:27:36,140 --> 00:27:38,460
And psi is a commonly used letter

763
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:40,020
to represent the state of a system.

764
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:42,020
Now the states of systems

765
00:27:42,020 --> 00:27:44,200
do change with time.

766
00:27:44,420 --> 00:27:46,000
So you have to think of these,

767
00:27:46,140 --> 00:27:46,880
these vectors,

768
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:49,060
as being functions of time.

769
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:49,620
They evolve.

770
00:27:50,380 --> 00:27:52,340
So let's put that in here

771
00:27:52,340 --> 00:27:53,380
in the following way.

772
00:27:53,540 --> 00:27:55,020
Psi of t,

773
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:57,080
this simply represents

