809
00:29:17,570 --> 00:29:18,820
Not necessarily final,

810
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,360
but the state at some time.

811
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:23,260
The basic postulate,

812
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:24,480
two basic postulates.

813
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:27,780
The first is that U is a linear operator.

814
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:29,940
That U is a linear operator

815
00:29:29,940 --> 00:29:31,740
and the same U

816
00:29:32,679 --> 00:29:33,980
for any state.

817
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:35,820
Whatever the initial state is,

818
00:29:36,740 --> 00:29:38,080
you put that here

819
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:40,360
and you hit it with the same U,

820
00:29:40,580 --> 00:29:41,640
the same operator.

821
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:42,220
In other words,

822
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:42,960
there is a,

823
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,240
this is called the time development operator.

824
00:29:45,980 --> 00:29:47,320
It's a linear operator

825
00:29:49,740 --> 00:29:51,820
and it evolves the state

826
00:29:51,820 --> 00:29:53,640
from one instant to another.

827
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:56,040
You could try to ask

828
00:29:56,040 --> 00:29:57,900
what would happen if you made a more

829
00:29:59,460 --> 00:30:00,580
general hypothesis.

830
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,180
For example,

831
00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:03,320
